11#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/source/packet_sequencer.h"
12
13#include "rtc_base/checks.h"
14
15namespace webrtc {
16
17namespace {
18// RED header is first byte of payload, if present.
19constexpr size_t kRedForFecHeaderLength = 1;
20
21// Timestamps use a 90kHz clock.
22constexpr uint32_t kTimestampTicksPerMs = 90;
23} // namespace
24
25PacketSequencer::PacketSequencer(uint32_t media_ssrc,
26 uint32_t rtx_ssrc,
27 bool require_marker_before_media_padding,
28 Clock* clock)
29 : media_ssrc_(media_ssrc),
30 rtx_ssrc_(rtx_ssrc),
31 require_marker_before_media_padding_(require_marker_before_media_padding),
32 clock_(clock),
33 media_sequence_number_(0),
34 rtx_sequence_number_(0),
35 last_payload_type_(-1),
36 last_rtp_timestamp_(0),
37 last_capture_time_ms_(0),
38 last_timestamp_time_ms_(0),
39 last_packet_marker_bit_(false) {}
40
41bool PacketSequencer::Sequence(RtpPacketToSend& packet) {
42 if (packet.packet_type() == RtpPacketMediaType::kPadding &&
43 !PopulatePaddingFields(packet)) {
44 // This padding packet can't be sent with current state, return without
45 // updating the sequence number.
46 return false;
47 }
48
49 if (packet.Ssrc() == media_ssrc_) {
50 packet.SetSequenceNumber(media_sequence_number_++);
51 if (packet.packet_type() != RtpPacketMediaType::kPadding) {
52 UpdateLastPacketState(packet);
53 }
54 return true;
55 }
56
57 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(packet.Ssrc(), rtx_ssrc_);
58 packet.SetSequenceNumber(rtx_sequence_number_++);
59 return true;
60}
61
62void PacketSequencer::SetRtpState(const RtpState& state) {
63 media_sequence_number_ = state.sequence_number;
64 last_rtp_timestamp_ = state.timestamp;
65 last_capture_time_ms_ = state.capture_time_ms;
66 last_timestamp_time_ms_ = state.last_timestamp_time_ms;
67}
68
69void PacketSequencer::PupulateRtpState(RtpState& state) const {
70 state.sequence_number = media_sequence_number_;
71 state.timestamp = last_rtp_timestamp_;
72 state.capture_time_ms = last_capture_time_ms_;
73 state.last_timestamp_time_ms = last_timestamp_time_ms_;
74}
75
76void PacketSequencer::UpdateLastPacketState(const RtpPacketToSend& packet) {
77 // Remember marker bit to determine if padding can be inserted with
78 // sequence number following |packet|.
79 last_packet_marker_bit_ = packet.Marker();
80 // Remember media payload type to use in the padding packet if rtx is
81 // disabled.
82 if (packet.is_red()) {
83 RTC_DCHECK_GE(packet.payload_size(), kRedForFecHeaderLength);
84 last_payload_type_ = packet.PayloadBuffer()[0];
85 } else {
86 last_payload_type_ = packet.PayloadType();
87 }
88 // Save timestamps to generate timestamp field and extensions for the padding.
89 last_rtp_timestamp_ = packet.Timestamp();
90 last_timestamp_time_ms_ = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
91 last_capture_time_ms_ = packet.capture_time_ms();
92}
93
94bool PacketSequencer::PopulatePaddingFields(RtpPacketToSend& packet) {
95 if (packet.Ssrc() == media_ssrc_) {
96 if (last_payload_type_ == -1) {
97 return false;
98 }
99
100 // Without RTX we can't send padding in the middle of frames.
101 // For audio marker bits doesn't mark the end of a frame and frames
102 // are usually a single packet, so for now we don't apply this rule
103 // for audio.
104 if (require_marker_before_media_padding_ && !last_packet_marker_bit_) {
105 return false;
106 }
107
108 packet.SetTimestamp(last_rtp_timestamp_);
109 packet.set_capture_time_ms(last_capture_time_ms_);
110 packet.SetPayloadType(last_payload_type_);
111 return true;
112 }
113
114 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(packet.Ssrc(), rtx_ssrc_);
115 if (packet.payload_size() > 0) {
116 // This is payload padding packet, don't update timestamp fields.
117 return true;
118 }
119
120 packet.SetTimestamp(last_rtp_timestamp_);
121 packet.set_capture_time_ms(last_capture_time_ms_);
122
123 // Only change the timestamp of padding packets sent over RTX.
124 // Padding only packets over RTP has to be sent as part of a media
125 // frame (and therefore the same timestamp).
126 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
127 if (last_timestamp_time_ms_ > 0) {
128 packet.SetTimestamp(packet.Timestamp() +
129 (now_ms - last_timestamp_time_ms_) *
130 kTimestampTicksPerMs);
131 if (packet.capture_time_ms() > 0) {
132 packet.set_capture_time_ms(packet.capture_time_ms() +
133 (now_ms - last_timestamp_time_ms_));
134 }
135 }
136
137 return true;
138}
